column5: Were going for 4 days in Nov. 7 guys. Any board members going?

I've been thinking of chasin the eyes on the 17th... Since I had put my old truck to rest, my wife mentioned we are visiting family that weekend in kingston. So I will be borrow her Grand Vitara to bring the boat out 1 more time before she goes away for the year  I need a new truck ASAP! LOL!
A bunch of us will be there the weekend after (23-25).  Hopefully the bite turns on for you. And stays on for us  :thumbsup_anim:
Thanks. I've read posts on a other site, things don't look good right now.

Just got back from picton. Spent the weekend there. Marked lots but managed only one pike out front of the cement plant. Heard of a few eyes 9 + lbs but not a lot of numbers. Good luck and looking forward to your post. Bill
Thanks Bill for the update. I heard things are picking up, a buddy was down for a day trip and caught 7 5LBs. and over.
Anybody hearing of many over 10lbs yet....???
I will be hunting ducks down there mid week. No fishing though.....  S.

I'll post when I get back Mike with pictures, if I get fish   I'm looking for the big mama for just a picture and she's back to swim another day. We just look for a big length & girth entree for the club. Then the get-together at night

May go tomorrow for my last trip.  Been out 5 days since Nov5th and it's been great.  Started a report but stuck at work now.  Will pop up something early week I think.  Fish are there, have been there, and are biting.  This week should be great too.

I hope you do...  I was asking because I haven't been seeing many reports yet....  I'm pounding nice walleye at home... 10-20 a night with lots of 6-7-8-9 pounders....  So I'm questioning going up to quinte next weekend....
Cool. I am questioning why I haven't started stalking you and fishing in our area.  Sadly, I haven't been out fishing since September.
Lol...  But I'm not getting the 10+ pounders you hear about in quinte....
Tybo got a beaut 18 pounder out of Quinte 5 or more years ago. I don't remember if it was a skin mount or a replica he had done but it was by far the largest I've ever seen.

10-20 a night, "wholly crap"   Fill me in on your secret. I just want to catch 1, but a big one   You must live near there Mike.  18 Lb'er, I can't even dream one that big Roy  I've been going to Quinte since a kid and I haven't beat my 11. As I say this week it's going to happen  I've had buds in MY boat that have caught 14's
Got a late start today, Just finished a few hours on the bay. 3 hours trolling 0 hits. I marked 8 balls of bait only no hooks.  Got 1 small one casting a jigging spoon.  Great day on the water....
